SIMPLE: headlong
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Headlong
<hw>Head"long`</hw> <pr>(-l⟦ocr⟧ng`; 115)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos>
<ety>[OE. <ets>hedling</ets>, <ets>hevedlynge</ets>; prob. confused with
E. <ets>long</ets>, <pos>a. & adv.</pos>]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>With the head foremost; headforemost; head first;
<as>as, to fall <ex>headlong</ex></as>.</def> <rj><au>Acts i.
18.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Rashly; precipitately; without
deliberation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Hastily; without delay or respite.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Headlong</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Headlong
<hw>Head"long</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Rash; precipitate;
<as>as, <ex>headlong</ex> folly</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Steep; precipitous.</def> <mark>[Poetic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Like a tower upon a <qex>headlong</qex> rock.</q>
<rj><qau>Byron.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Head-lugged</ent>⟦br⟧
